        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Prakash Surya",
          "email": "surya1@llnl.gov",
          "date": "2011-09-27 23:15:37.000000000",
          "tz": -420
        },
        "subject": "LU-723 Call LB_PATH_LDISKFS then LB_CONFIG_MODULES",
        "message": "LU-723 Call LB_PATH_LDISKFS then LB_CONFIG_MODULES\n\nThe LB_PATH_LDISKFS macro needs to be called prior to the\nLB_CONFIG_MODULES. This is because the LB_CONFIG_MODULES calls\nLC_PROG_LINUX which depends on the LDISKFS_DIR variable being set; and\nthis variable is set in the LB_PATH_LDISKFS macro.\n\nAs a result of the above, the location of the AC_DEFINE which provides\nthe HAVE_EXT4_LDISKFS macro had to be moved to a more appropriate\nlocation (from LB_PATH_LDISKFS to LB_HAVE_EXT4_ENABLED). The move was\nnecessary because of the tightly coupled relationship between the\nLDISKFS_DIR, LB_HAVE_EXT4_ENABLED, LB_PATH_LDISKFS macros.\n\nTo summarize the order of execution:\n 1. LB_PATH_LDISKFS\n 2. LDISKFS_DIR          (set in LB_PATH_LDISKFS)\n 3. LB_CONFIG_MODULES\n 4. LC_PROG_LINUX        (needs LDISKFS_DIR)\n 5. LB_HAVE_EXT4_ENABLED (needs LDISKFS_DIR)\n 6. HAVE_EXT4_LDISKFS    (set in LB_HAVE_EXT4_LDISKFS)\n\nSigned-off-by: Prakash Surya <surya1@llnl.gov>\nChange-Id: Id22d38ac40b0f88c37379c35556c43536b4fe2f1\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
